<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-699-677  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 699 677.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Magazine  Dec 25 1990 v9 n22 p508(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Chapter and verse on disk. (Seasonal picks: the best of AfterHours) (software gift suggestions) (After Hours) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Matzkin, Jonathan; Zelnick, Nathaniel.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   NASSCO Inc. (Products)BibleSoft (Products).andO;Product:   CompuBible (Data base) (Marketing)PC Study Bible (Computer program) (Marketing).andO;Topic:     ReligionSoftware packagesUser Interface.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>CHAPTER AND VERSE ON DISK Even the Holy Bible has found its way onto thepersonal computer.andP;  There are many fine software packages that offer help tothose who turn to the Good Book for insight, solace, or research.andP;  Twooutstanding examples, which make appropriate holiday gifts in our electronicage, are Compubible ($99) from NASSCO Inc. and PC Study Bible ($149.95) fromBibleSoft.andP;  Compubible has a very well-thought-out interface that allows upto four simultaneous windows for comparisons of different Bible versions.andO;The software comes with your choice of translation (additional Bible versionsare $79 each).andP;  Windows can also compare different books and verses withinthe same Bible version.andP;  PC Study Bible also does windows, but its greateststrength is its inclusion of four complete Bible versions (The King James,The New International, The American Standard, and Nave's Topical Bible) forits initial purchase price.andO;</TEXT></DOC>